Request Verification:
- Confirm termination date from HR
- Verify manager approval for offboarding
- Determine if immediate or scheduled termination
- Note any data retention or access requirements

Pre-Termination Tasks:
- Identify all systems and applications user has access to
- Document shared resources user manages
- Identify mailbox delegates or shared mailbox access
- Note any pending work or critical files

{% if termination_type == 'immediate' %}
Immediate Termination:
- Disable Active Directory account immediately
- Revoke VPN and remote access
- Disable MFA methods
- Force sign-out from all active sessions
- Block mobile device access via MDM
{% endif %}

Account Disabling:
- Disable (do not delete) Active Directory account
- Remove from all security groups
- Disable Microsoft 365 / Google Workspace account
- Revoke application-specific access
- Remove from distribution lists

Email Handling:
- Set up mailbox forwarding to manager (if approved)
- Configure out-of-office auto-reply
- Convert mailbox to shared mailbox (if retention needed)
- Document mailbox retention period
- Remove email from mobile devices

Data Management:
- Backup user's OneDrive/Google Drive
- Transfer ownership of shared files to manager
- Archive or reassign shared resources
- Document any data retention requirements

Application Access Removal:
- Revoke access to all business applications
- Remove from CRM, ERP, HR systems
- Disable VPN and remote access profiles
- Remove from project management tools

Equipment Return:
- Send equipment return instructions (if remote)
- Schedule equipment pickup or drop-off
- Document expected equipment to be returned
- Update asset management for returned items

Post-Offboarding:
- Verify all access has been revoked
- Test that account cannot authenticate
- Confirm equipment return tracking
- Document completion with all actions taken
- Archive offboarding record per retention policy
